.TH "frwr_map" 9 "frwr_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
frwr_map \- Register a memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rpcrdma_mr_seg *" frwr_map
.BI "(struct rpcrdma_xprt *r_xprt "  ","
.BI "struct rpcrdma_mr_seg *seg "  ","
.BI "int nsegs "  ","
.BI "bool writing "  ","
.BI "__be32 xid "  ","
.BI "struct rpcrdma_mr *mr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r_xprt" 12
controlling transport
.IP "seg" 12
memory region co-ordinates
.IP "nsegs" 12
number of segments remaining
.IP "writing" 12
true when RDMA Write will be used
.IP "xid" 12
XID of RPC using the registered memory
.IP "mr" 12
MR to fill in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prepare a REG_MR Work Request to register a memory region
for remote access via RDMA READ or RDMA WRITE.

Returns the next segment or a negative errno pointer.
On success, \fImr\fP is filled in.
